}$. It follows for\n$E<10^{-7}$ that the geostrophic turbulent interior remains the flux bottleneck\nin rapidly rotating Rayleigh-B\\'enard convection. For $E\\sim10^{-7}$, where DNS\nand asymptotic simulations agree quantitatively, it is found that the effects\nof Ekman pumping are sufficiently strong to influence the heat transport with\ndiminished exponent $\\alpha \\approx 1.2$ and $Nu-1 \\propto (Ra E^{4/3}\n)^{1.2}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 15 Apr 2017 23:20:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-09-13"}
